# Authors

This file lists the contributors to the Grafana Query IDE project.

## Project Lead & Primary Developer

* **Richard Kiene** - Project founder, lead developer, and maintainer
  - Core application architecture and design
  - VS Code-like interface implementation
  - PromQL and InfluxQL syntax highlighting and autocomplete
  - Grafana API integration and proxy server
  - Connection management and secure authentication
  - Schema explorer and data visualization
  - Query history and variable systems
  - Cross-platform Electron application setup
  - AI/ML analytics integration with Ollama
  - Time series preprocessing and anomaly detection
  - Production build configuration and deployment

## Design & Branding

* **Richard Kiene** - User interface design and branding
  - Time Buddy mascot and logo design
  - Application icons and visual identity
  - User experience design and workflow optimization

## Technical Contributors

* **Richard Kiene** - Core development and architecture
  - JavaScript/Node.js backend development
  - Electron desktop application framework
  - Express.js proxy server implementation
  - CodeMirror editor integration
  - Chart.js visualization components
  - GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline
  - Multi-platform build and release automation

## AI/ML Analytics

* **Richard Kiene** - AI-powered anomaly detection system
  - Ollama LLM integration for time series analysis
  - Visual analysis mode with chart-based insights
  - Intelligent data subsampling algorithms
  - Multi-modal AI model support (Llama, Gemma, etc.)
  - Saved analysis tracking and management

## Quality Assurance & Testing

* **Richard Kiene** - Quality assurance and testing
  - Manual testing across all supported platforms
  - User acceptance testing and feedback integration
  - Performance optimization and bug fixes

## Documentation

* **Richard Kiene** - Technical documentation and user guides
  - README.md and project documentation
  - Code comments and architectural documentation
  - User guides and troubleshooting documentation

---

## How to Contribute

We welcome contributions from the community! If you'd like to contribute to this project:

1. **Fork the repository** on GitHub
2. **Create a feature branch** for your changes
3. **Make your changes** with clear commit messages
4. **Add tests** if applicable
5. **Submit a pull request** with a detailed description

### Areas for Contribution

- Additional query language support (LogQL, SQL variants)
- New AI models and analysis algorithms
- Enhanced visualizations and chart types
- Performance optimizations
- Bug fixes and user experience improvements
- Documentation improvements
- Internationalization and localization

### Recognition

All contributors who submit accepted pull requests will be added to this AUTHORS file with appropriate attribution for their contributions.

